        <prov id="DLM330670" irdnumbering="no" toc="yes" skeleton="no">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">6</label>
          <heading>Rules</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov deletion-status="repealed" skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text/>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>A board may from time to time, by resolution, make, alter, or rescind any rules not inconsistent with this Act for all or any of the following purposes:</text>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">a</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>prescribing the procedure to be followed at any meeting of the board or committee of the board or community arts council:</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
                <label-para skeleton="no">
                  <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">b</label>
                  <para>
                    <text>such other purposes as may be deemed necessary or expedient for duly carrying out the work of the board or of any committee thereof or of any community arts council.</text>
                  </para>
                </label-para>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <notes>
            <history>
              <history-note id="DLM330671"><amended-provision>Schedule 1 clause 6(1)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>repealed</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 January 2005</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM331111">section 200</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Crown Entities Act 2004</amending-leg> (2004 No 115).</history-note>
            </history>
          </notes>
        </prov>
        <prov id="DLM330672" irdnumbering="no" toc="yes" skeleton="no">
          <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">7</label>
          <heading>Committees</heading>
          <prov.body>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">1</label>
              <para>
                <text><struckoutwords/>A board may from time to time, by resolution, appoint, alter, discharge, continue, or reconstitute any committee to advise<struckoutwords/> a board on such matters relating to<struckoutwords/> a board's functions and powers as may be delegated to the committee under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM330677">clause 8</intref></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">2</label>
              <para>
                <text>Every committee shall consist of such number of persons as<struckoutwords/> the board thinks fit to enable the committee to carry out such functions and powers as may be delegated to the committee under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="DLM330677">clause 8</intref></citation>.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">3</label>
              <para>
                <text>Any person may be appointed to be a member of a committee, whether or not that person is a member of<struckoutwords/> a board.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
            <subprov skeleton="no">
              <label auto.number="no" denominator="yes">4</label>
              <para>
                <text>Subject to this Act, to any rules made by a board, and to any direction given by the Council or a board, every committee of the board may regulate its own procedure.</text>
              </para>
            </subprov>
          </prov.body>
          <notes>
            <history>
              <history-note id="DLM330673"><amended-provision>Schedule 1 clause 7(1)</amended-provision>: <amending-operation>amended</amending-operation>, on <amendment-date>25 January 2005</amendment-date>, by <amending-provision href="DLM331111">section 200</amending-provision> of the <amending-leg>Crown Entities Act 2004</amending-leg> (2004 No 115).</history-note>
